column3:
> Can you squash these together?

Okay, done. The rebase of 9c288e3 into e04b2db is done in 141f97a0f8bbbfea55a113aff25f4f88f984f7ad.
I don't really see the point. We can generate an infinity of these cleanup-whitespace commits.\n
I also think cleanup-commits with no reasonable benefit (better code-readability, etc.) makes just no sense. Especially if they are as small as this commit is.\n
I agree, but starting a discussion about this type of commits (which come back from time to time anyway) takes more effort than reviewing and merging them.\n
